DAMATURU – The National Emergency Management Agency (NEMA), today decorated Yobe state Governor, His Excellency Hon. Mai Mala Buni, as its ambassador in Disaster Management, in recognition of his government’s efficient and timely response to disaster. Governor Buni was decorated at the National Headquarters of the Agency when he paid a working visit to the agency to solicit support to victims of flood Disaster in the state. The governor said Yobe state government needs the support of the Agency because of the massive damage suffered by the affected communities across the state. He explained that many houses, farmlands and livestock were lost to the floods. Similarly, the road linking some local government areas were washed away by the flood. “I have directed the State Emergency Management Agency to provide immediate support to the victims however, we need your support to resettle the victims” he said. POLL Governor Buni solicited for the support of the Agency to provide succour to make life more meaningful to the victims. The Director General of the Agency, Mustapha Habib Ahmed, assured that NEMA would partner the state government to support the victims and complement the efforts of the state government. He commended Yobe state government for the efficient and unparalleled response to disaster management. “Let me state without fear of contradiction that Yobe state government is a pace setter in disaster management in the country. “Your State Emergency Management Agency (SEMA) is exceptionally doing well in providing succour to victims of disaster and this makes us very proud. He said staff of the agency have already been drafted to the affected communities.